our and patronage of the arts."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodger","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Roger  , in part from the surname derived from the given name in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":0,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":9,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":44,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Roger de Fulthorpe was born about 1215, in Durham, England. She had at least 1 son with Sir Roger de Fulthorpe."},"et":{"about 1215–":"umbes 1215–Surnud","1210–1240":"1210–1240","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1215–Female":"1215–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","about 1215":"umbes 1215","1210":"1210","1285":"1285","1240":"1240","Durham, England":"Durham, England","Fulthorpe, Darlington, Durham, England":"Darlington, Durham, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1215–":"noin 1215–Kuollut","1210–1240":"1210–1240","1240–1285":"1240–1285","1215–Female":"1215–Kuollut","1259":"1259","12